WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:03.086
(all)
♪ Get your spy on ♪

00:03.169 --> 00:04.754
♪ Spy on ♪

00:04.838 --> 00:07.424
♪ You're on a mission
with a Twist and Shout ♪

00:07.507 --> 00:08.925
♪ Shout! ♪

00:09.008 --> 00:11.219
♪ Kiki and Marina spy it up
to work it out ♪

00:11.302 --> 00:12.262
♪ Out! ♪

00:12.345 --> 00:14.097
♪ Bounce with our sidekick, Bo ♪

00:14.180 --> 00:15.765
♪ Gadgets on the go ♪

00:15.849 --> 00:18.226
♪ Who's the first at the scene
of the crime? ♪

00:18.309 --> 00:19.519
♪ Fresh Beats! ♪

00:19.602 --> 00:23.231
♪ Solving the mystery
every time ♪

00:23.314 --> 00:27.610
♪ Trouble's no match for
the Fresh Beat Band of Spies ♪

00:27.694 --> 00:29.404
♪ Get your hands up high ♪

00:29.487 --> 00:31.614
♪ Find a cool disguise ♪

00:31.698 --> 00:34.033
♪<i> Fresh Beat Band of Spies ♪</i>

00:34.117 --> 00:35.577
♪ Get your spy on ♪

00:40.623 --> 00:42.834
[bell ringing]

00:42.917 --> 00:44.502
[siren blaring]

00:44.586 --> 00:45.837
Rubberface Rudy escaped!

00:45.920 --> 00:47.213
The man of a million faces?

00:47.297 --> 00:49.632
The mad master
of mysterious disguises?

00:49.716 --> 00:50.967
That's the one.

00:51.050 --> 00:53.011
Everyone report to the
Chief's office right away!

00:56.389 --> 00:57.432
[rapid mumbling]

00:57.515 --> 01:00.685
Rubberface Rudy,
you've done it again.

01:00.769 --> 01:01.728
Face it.

01:01.811 --> 01:04.313
I am amazing!

01:04.397 --> 01:05.482
[smooches]

01:06.524 --> 01:07.650
[upbeat music]

01:07.734 --> 01:10.236
(Twist)
♪ Are you r-r-r-r-ready? ♪

01:10.320 --> 01:11.654
♪ Move it, move it ♪

01:11.738 --> 01:13.531
- ♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh ♪
- ♪ Hey! ♪

01:13.615 --> 01:15.533
- ♪ Here we go! ♪
- ♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh ♪

01:15.617 --> 01:17.202
♪ We've got a green light ♪

01:17.285 --> 01:17.786
♪ We're gonna take a ride ♪

01:17.869 --> 01:19.579
♪ Come on! ♪

01:19.662 --> 01:20.747
♪ What are you waiting for? ♪

01:20.830 --> 01:23.082
♪ It's time to move it ♪

01:23.166 --> 01:24.751
♪ It's time to groove it ♪

01:24.834 --> 01:26.002
♪ Are you ready? ♪

01:26.085 --> 01:27.045
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:27.128 --> 01:28.213
Hold up, Fresh Beats!

01:28.296 --> 01:29.297
[Bo chatters]

01:29.380 --> 01:30.298
(all)
Our spy watches!

01:30.381 --> 01:33.009
Fresh Beats!
Report to headquarters.

01:33.092 --> 01:34.385
I've got a mission for you.

01:34.469 --> 01:36.638
It could be
your toughest one yet.

01:36.721 --> 01:37.722
We're on it, Reed.

01:37.806 --> 01:38.973
{\an3}Fresh Beats
to headquarters.

01:39.057 --> 01:39.098
{\an3}Let's go!

01:41.434 --> 01:42.519
{\an3}Reed?

01:42.602 --> 01:43.520
Fresh Beats!

01:43.603 --> 01:45.271
[all scream]

01:45.355 --> 01:49.567
{\an3}Commissioner Goldstar
has an urgent message for you.

01:49.651 --> 01:51.653
[electronic whirring, buzzing]

01:51.736 --> 01:55.698
[mysterious music]

01:55.782 --> 01:56.825
♪ ♪

01:56.908 --> 01:57.909
Ha, ha!

01:57.992 --> 01:59.869
[thuds]
Oof!

01:59.953 --> 02:01.371
Every single time.

02:01.454 --> 02:02.413
[electricity zaps]

02:02.497 --> 02:03.373
Fresh Beats,

02:03.456 --> 02:05.917
we need your help to find...

02:06.000 --> 02:07.752
Rubberface Rudy.

02:07.836 --> 02:09.127
- Whoo.
- The man of a million faces?

02:09.211 --> 02:12.215
The mad master
of mysterious disguises?

02:12.298 --> 02:13.258
That's the one.

02:13.341 --> 02:14.551
He's escaped,

02:14.634 --> 02:16.928
and the police
can't find him anywhere.

02:17.011 --> 02:20.431
Your mission:
find Rubberface Rudy.

02:20.515 --> 02:23.268
{\an1}Rubberface Rudy always
disguises himself

02:23.351 --> 02:24.602
for his crimes.

02:24.686 --> 02:26.729
This is how he robbed
the skateboard store.

02:26.813 --> 02:28.106
[rapid mumbling]

02:30.483 --> 02:32.402
This is how he robbed
the baby store.

02:32.485 --> 02:35.947
[crying]

02:36.030 --> 02:36.656
[rapid mumbling]

02:36.739 --> 02:40.118
[laughs evilly]

02:40.201 --> 02:44.414
And this is how he robbed
the history museum.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.082
[rapid mumbling]

02:46.165 --> 02:47.458
Rawr!

02:47.542 --> 02:49.919
(Shout)
Oh, he's good.

02:50.003 --> 02:53.339
{\an3}Rubberface Rudy can pretend
to be anyone.

02:53.423 --> 02:56.092
He could be someone
in this very room.

02:57.093 --> 02:58.011
{\an1}Um...

02:58.094 --> 02:59.012
{\an1}Twist?

02:59.095 --> 03:00.680
{\an3}Yes, Kiki?

03:00.763 --> 03:02.932
{\an3}If that's who
you really are.

03:03.016 --> 03:03.641
Ears look like Kiki,

03:03.725 --> 03:05.727
nose looks like Kiki,

03:05.810 --> 03:08.438
hair, just like Kiki,

03:08.521 --> 03:11.065
{\an3}but how can you prove
that you're Kiki?

03:11.149 --> 03:12.483
{\an1}Um...

03:13.902 --> 03:16.154
♪ This is how Kiki sings! ♪

03:16.237 --> 03:19.699
Okay, you're Kiki
all right.

03:19.782 --> 03:20.617
{\an3}Hmm.

03:20.700 --> 03:22.577
Uh, Bo Monkey?

03:22.660 --> 03:24.579
{\an1}[yelps]
I'm the real Twist.

03:24.662 --> 03:25.622
{\an1}Ooh!

03:25.705 --> 03:26.664
{\an1}Seriously.
I am.

03:26.748 --> 03:27.165
{\an1}Ah!

03:27.248 --> 03:27.749
Okay, let go.

03:27.832 --> 03:28.958
Sorry, Twist.

03:29.042 --> 03:31.169
How are we going to find him

03:31.252 --> 03:32.420
if he can make himself

03:32.503 --> 03:34.964
look like anyone
or anything?

03:35.048 --> 03:38.509
{\an3}This is a mission
for the Fresh Beat Band...

03:38.593 --> 03:40.845
(all)
Of Spies.

03:40.929 --> 03:41.512
Time to spy it up!

03:41.596 --> 03:43.514
Ooh-ooh!

03:43.598 --> 03:45.975
[intense music]

03:46.059 --> 03:47.435
[watches beeping]

03:47.518 --> 03:51.064
♪ ♪

03:52.649 --> 03:55.735
Okay, fake Fresh Beats,
put on your disguises.

03:55.818 --> 03:58.780
Time to rob it up!
[laughs]

03:58.863 --> 04:00.698
[rapid mumbling]

04:00.782 --> 04:02.408
Twist disguise, on!

04:02.492 --> 04:04.494
Marina disguise, on!

04:04.577 --> 04:06.496
Kiki disguise, on!

04:07.413 --> 04:09.624
Ah, the Fresh Beat Band.

04:09.707 --> 04:11.501
What can I do for you today?

04:11.584 --> 04:12.168
We'll take that.

04:12.251 --> 04:13.252
{\an1}And that.
Thank you.

04:13.336 --> 04:15.713
[stutters]
But you can't rob us!

04:15.797 --> 04:17.382
You're the Fresh Beat Band!

04:17.464 --> 04:18.548
That's right.

04:18.632 --> 04:20.969
The Fresh Beat Band...

04:21.052 --> 04:24.097
(all)
Of bank robbers.

04:26.349 --> 04:27.934
Shoutstanding...

04:28.017 --> 04:30.103
bank robbery!

04:30.186 --> 04:31.980
[Rubberface laughs evilly]

04:32.063 --> 04:35.441
No one will ever trust
those musical spies again.

04:35.525 --> 04:36.484
[rapid mumbling]

04:36.567 --> 04:37.944
[laughs]

04:38.027 --> 04:40.363
Soon we'll be able to commit
all the crimes we want

04:40.446 --> 04:42.281
without ever having
to worry about

04:42.365 --> 04:44.158
the Fresh Beat Band.

04:44.242 --> 04:45.118
Face it.

04:45.201 --> 04:46.786
I'm a genius.

04:46.869 --> 04:47.954
Arrrgh!

04:48.037 --> 04:49.998
'Tis a fine scheme, so say I,

04:50.081 --> 04:51.124
Captain Arrrgh!

04:51.207 --> 04:54.711
♪ The most feared
singing pirate captain ♪

04:54.794 --> 04:58.131
♪ In the world! ♪

04:58.214 --> 04:58.923
[clucks]

04:59.007 --> 05:00.883
Me chicken, Poulet, agrees.

05:00.967 --> 05:04.387
Yi-Haw!
[laughs]

05:04.470 --> 05:06.055
Rubberface, I'm happier

05:06.139 --> 05:07.932
than a bucket of beans
to be in your posse!

05:08.016 --> 05:10.560
What do you say, Snort?

05:10.643 --> 05:11.436
[snorts, neighs]

05:11.519 --> 05:15.064
[laughs evilly]
Von Winning!

05:15.148 --> 05:16.065
[Snort neighs]

05:16.149 --> 05:17.775
Um, not a big von deal,

05:17.859 --> 05:20.278
but when I,
Champ von Champ von...

05:20.361 --> 05:24.073
Marina Champ, agreed
that my beautiful mansion

05:24.157 --> 05:26.743
could be our von lair,
I did not expect

05:26.826 --> 05:29.746
von chickens und horses!

05:29.829 --> 05:30.246
[splat]

05:30.329 --> 05:31.914
Und eggs!

05:31.998 --> 05:35.668
Guess the yolk's
on you, Champy!

05:35.752 --> 05:37.545
Von harrumph.

05:37.628 --> 05:39.589
{\an1}One more big robbery
will make sure

05:39.672 --> 05:42.842
the Fresh Beats go away
for a good, long time.

05:42.925 --> 05:45.011
So hold onto the disguises
I gave you,

05:45.094 --> 05:47.430
and keep working
on your Fresh Beat voices!

05:47.513 --> 05:49.390
Boy howdy!

05:49.474 --> 05:50.600
{\an1}Arrrgh!

05:50.683 --> 05:51.976
Auf wieder-jailed!

05:52.060 --> 05:56.522
[all laughing evilly]

05:56.606 --> 05:56.856
[splat]

05:56.939 --> 05:58.441
{\an3}Ugh!

05:58.524 --> 05:59.442
Are you von kidding me?

06:03.321 --> 06:06.407
Everyone is talking
about the Fresh Beat band...

06:06.491 --> 06:08.242
{\an1}Guys, look.
She's talking about us!

06:08.326 --> 06:09.827
{\an3}Ha!
Shoutstanding!

06:09.911 --> 06:12.455
Because they're wanted
for robbing a bank.

06:12.538 --> 06:13.456
Shoutrageous!

06:13.539 --> 06:15.958
Whoa!
We robbed a bank?

06:16.042 --> 06:16.793
That wasn't very nice.

06:16.876 --> 06:19.253
Twist, we did not rob a bank.

06:19.337 --> 06:20.546
Oh, yes, they did!

06:20.630 --> 06:22.715
The footage from the bank
security camera

06:22.799 --> 06:25.968
clearly shows
the Fresh Beat Band.

06:26.052 --> 06:28.638
Shoutstanding...
bank robbery!

06:28.721 --> 06:29.806
{\an3}Shout!

06:29.889 --> 06:31.307
You did rob a bank!

06:31.390 --> 06:32.850
That wasn't me!

06:32.934 --> 06:34.143
It just looked like me...

06:34.227 --> 06:35.770
and sounded like me.

06:35.853 --> 06:38.022
{\an3}And said "shoutstanding"
like you.

06:38.106 --> 06:39.482
That's a lot of "like yous".

06:39.565 --> 06:41.067
{\an1}Wait, but who
could make themselves

06:41.150 --> 06:43.236
{\an1}look and sound
exactly like Shout?

06:43.319 --> 06:44.195
{\an3}[ding]

06:44.278 --> 06:45.321
Rubberface Rudy!

06:45.404 --> 06:47.323
He's the man
of a million disguises.

06:47.406 --> 06:48.199
Oh, this is terrible.

06:48.282 --> 06:50.993
People think we're robbers.

06:51.077 --> 06:52.495
We have to prove
we didn't do it.

06:52.578 --> 06:55.039
Well, the best way to do that
is to catch the real robbers.

06:55.123 --> 06:57.291
Let's go see if they left
any clues at the bank.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.502
But everyone thinks
we just robbed that bank.

06:59.585 --> 07:00.962
You're right, Kiki.

07:01.045 --> 07:01.921
We're gonna have
to search for clues...

07:02.004 --> 07:04.048
undercover.

07:05.424 --> 07:06.634
(Marina)
All right.

07:06.717 --> 07:07.760
I'm a janitor,

07:07.844 --> 07:08.845
Kiki's a window-cleaner,

07:08.928 --> 07:10.429
and Shout's a wrestling fan.

07:10.513 --> 07:12.265
Twist, where's
your disguise?

07:12.348 --> 07:15.351
Prepare to be amazed.

07:15.434 --> 07:16.435
<i>Voila!</i>

07:16.519 --> 07:18.187
We're a very tall,
very dapper,

07:18.271 --> 07:21.524
mustached monkey man.

07:21.607 --> 07:22.608
{\an1}[yelps]

07:22.692 --> 07:24.235
Ow!
[chuckles]

07:24.318 --> 07:24.569
With bellybutton eyes.

07:26.487 --> 07:28.072
(Marina)
Here we are!

07:28.156 --> 07:32.702
Just some regular old,
ordinary bank customers.

07:32.785 --> 07:35.163
Here to do some totally
normal banking.

07:35.246 --> 07:36.164
Yep!

07:36.247 --> 07:38.708
Bankity, banky,
bank, bank, bank, bank.

07:38.791 --> 07:41.252
[chattering, repeating Twist]

07:43.045 --> 07:44.088
{\an1}[whispers]
Find something?

07:44.172 --> 07:45.381
{\an3}An egg.

07:45.464 --> 07:46.716
{\an1}[chatters]

07:46.799 --> 07:49.218
{\an1}So we're looking
for a bank-robbing

07:49.302 --> 07:50.636
Easter Bunny.

07:50.720 --> 07:53.514
I did not see that coming.

07:53.598 --> 07:55.391
Ooh, a feather!

07:55.474 --> 07:55.892
[electronic whirring]

07:55.975 --> 07:57.727
Hey, Marina!

07:57.810 --> 07:58.978
{\an3}Ooh.
Whatcha doin'?

07:59.061 --> 08:00.771
{\an1}Copying the security tape
so we can give it

08:00.855 --> 08:01.230
a closer look.

08:01.314 --> 08:03.065
[chattering]

08:03.149 --> 08:04.692
{\an1}Got it.
Fresh Beats, let's go!

08:04.775 --> 08:05.651
- Got it.
- Right behind you.

08:08.237 --> 08:09.864
Whoa, whoa!

08:09.947 --> 08:11.032
[screams]
Ah!

08:11.115 --> 08:12.825
That man's head just fell off!

08:12.909 --> 08:14.911
And it's a... monkey!

08:14.994 --> 08:18.414
{\an6}(bank teller)
That's the Fresh Beat Band
of bank robbers!

08:18.497 --> 08:20.625
They're trying
to rob the bank again!

08:20.708 --> 08:22.335
Help! Police!

08:22.418 --> 08:23.753
[whoosh]

08:23.836 --> 08:25.087
[panting]

08:25.171 --> 08:26.214
Reed!

08:26.964 --> 08:28.883
Fresh Beats!

08:28.966 --> 08:30.343
(all)
Reed!

08:30.426 --> 08:32.678
The whole city thinks
you robbed that bank.

08:32.761 --> 08:33.679
We know.

08:33.763 --> 08:35.139
{\an1}We've got to
clear our names.

08:35.222 --> 08:36.140
{\an3}And soon!

08:36.224 --> 08:37.099
We found some clues
at the bank.

08:37.183 --> 08:39.101
I found this egg.

08:39.184 --> 08:40.727
Looks like
a chicken egg,

08:40.811 --> 08:41.437
but let's make sure.

08:41.520 --> 08:43.813
{\an1}Sweet!
So do we sit on it

08:43.898 --> 08:44.273
and keep it warm
till it hatches?

08:44.357 --> 08:44.982
First dibs!

08:45.066 --> 08:47.026
No!

08:47.109 --> 08:48.986
I'll use the egg detector.

08:49.070 --> 08:51.072
[electronic buzzing, beeping]

08:51.155 --> 08:52.281
Definitely a chicken egg.

08:52.365 --> 08:55.368
{\an3}Oh, then this is definitely
a chicken feather.

08:55.451 --> 08:58.120
Why would anyone bring
a chicken to the bank?

08:58.204 --> 08:59.247
Maybe the security tape
will help.

08:59.330 --> 09:02.041
[electronic whirring]

09:02.124 --> 09:02.667
(Shout)
Freeze it!

09:02.750 --> 09:04.210
Let's zoom in.

09:05.753 --> 09:06.796
Look, on the tail!

09:06.879 --> 09:08.297
It looks like another feather.

09:08.381 --> 09:10.299
{\an3}Hmm...
so we found a chicken egg

09:10.383 --> 09:11.634
and a chicken feather,

09:11.717 --> 09:14.804
{\an3}and the fake monkey
has a feather on it...

09:14.887 --> 09:16.472
{\an1}I totally see where
you're going with this.

09:16.555 --> 09:19.558
{\an1}It must be a mutant
half-monkey, half-chicken alien

09:19.642 --> 09:20.935
from another planet.

09:21.018 --> 09:23.187
{\an3}Or, it's a chicken
disguised as a monkey!

09:23.271 --> 09:25.231
{\an1}[laughing]
Okay.

09:25.314 --> 09:27.817
Now, that's bananas.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.360
{\an3}Brainstorm!

09:29.443 --> 09:31.529
{\an3}We'll use the chicken
recognition system.

09:31.612 --> 09:35.908
Kiki, put the feather
on the scanner.

09:35.992 --> 09:37.660
[electronic buzzing]

09:37.743 --> 09:39.328
[clucking]

09:39.412 --> 09:40.162
[ding]

09:40.246 --> 09:42.290
[gasps]
That's it!

09:42.373 --> 09:43.374
Poulet!

09:43.457 --> 09:45.293
The chicken who belongs
to Captain Arrrgh?

09:45.376 --> 09:50.131
♪ The most feared singing
pirate captain in the world! ♪

09:50.214 --> 09:54.093
{\an1}So the guy pretending to be me
is a fierce pirate captain?

09:54.176 --> 09:55.011
Yeah, I can totally see that.

09:55.094 --> 09:56.887
{\an1}Rubberface Rudy
and Captain Arrrgh:

09:56.971 --> 10:00.766
{\an1}two of the world's worst
bad guys teaming up together.

10:00.850 --> 10:04.687
Fresh Beats!
It's Commissioner Goldstar.

10:04.770 --> 10:06.522
Get over to the diamond store.

10:06.605 --> 10:07.648
It's urgent!

10:07.732 --> 10:08.024
Another robbery?

10:08.107 --> 10:10.026
{\an3}Must be!

10:10.109 --> 10:11.777
Let's go get those imposters.

10:11.861 --> 10:13.237
Good luck, Fresh Beats!

10:13.779 --> 10:14.697
[rapid mumbling]

10:14.780 --> 10:16.907
{\an3}That will bring
those spies running.

10:16.991 --> 10:21.078
{\an3}Okay, fake Fresh Beats,
get in that diamond store

10:21.162 --> 10:22.371
{\an3}and grab all the diamonds
you can carry.

10:22.455 --> 10:25.166
[sings]
Von Grabbing!

10:25.249 --> 10:29.462
And soon the real Fresh Beats
will be behind bars.

10:29.545 --> 10:29.920
[rapid mumbling]

10:30.004 --> 10:32.006
Face it.

10:32.089 --> 10:33.257
I'm a genius.

10:34.300 --> 10:35.301
May we help?

10:35.384 --> 10:37.803
{\an3}That's the Fresh Beat
band of robbers!

10:37.887 --> 10:38.971
{\an3}[yells]
Ah!

10:39.055 --> 10:40.514
[sings]
You're absolutely right!

10:40.598 --> 10:44.518
This here's a robbery, y'all.

10:44.602 --> 10:46.062
Time to steal it up!

10:46.145 --> 10:47.605
You'll never get away with this!

10:47.688 --> 10:49.732
Too small, too small...

10:49.815 --> 10:50.941
I want the biggest
von diamond!

10:51.025 --> 10:54.570
I be wantin' the biggest
collection of diamonds

10:54.653 --> 10:55.446
♪ In the world! ♪

10:55.529 --> 10:58.741
{\an1}I say we steal
the whole store.

10:58.824 --> 10:59.784
Shh! Let's go!

10:59.867 --> 11:01.744
Out the back door!

11:01.827 --> 11:02.203
[Poulet clucks]

11:02.286 --> 11:05.039
♪ ♪

11:05.122 --> 11:06.040
[ding]

11:06.123 --> 11:08.292
[cluck]

11:08.376 --> 11:10.920
♪ ♪

11:11.003 --> 11:12.588
Oh, they're back!

11:12.671 --> 11:15.216
{\an3}They always return
to the scene of the crime.

11:15.299 --> 11:16.675
{\an1}So soon?

11:16.759 --> 11:19.762
{\an3}Get out of here,
you Fresh Beat Band of robbers!

11:19.845 --> 11:21.097
No, no, no!

11:21.180 --> 11:23.599
{\an1}We're here to save you,
not rob you.

11:23.682 --> 11:24.600
Who did this?

11:24.683 --> 11:25.643
You did.

11:25.726 --> 11:26.685
You lassoed us
and stole our diamonds.

11:26.769 --> 11:28.729
Hey! Looks like
they dropped a diamond.

11:28.813 --> 11:31.774
And these bags
for carrying their loot.

11:31.857 --> 11:32.983
[chatters]

11:33.067 --> 11:34.318
Hold it right there,
Fresh Beats.

11:34.402 --> 11:36.987
Oh, Commissioner Goldstar!

11:37.071 --> 11:39.615
What is going on here?

11:39.698 --> 11:45.121
♪ ♪

11:45.204 --> 11:47.248
This does not look good.

11:47.331 --> 11:49.208
Commissioner!

11:49.291 --> 11:51.877
Arrest these robbers!

11:51.961 --> 11:53.796
Commissioner, we didn't do this.

11:53.879 --> 11:55.589
It was the fake Fresh Beat Band.

11:55.673 --> 11:58.551
Rubberface Rudy, Captain Arrrgh,
and two other villains.

11:58.634 --> 11:59.135
[clucks]

11:59.218 --> 12:01.554
Yuck!

12:01.637 --> 12:04.014
{\an3}And Captain Arrrgh's
fierce chicken, Poulet,

12:04.098 --> 12:05.141
dressed as Bo.

12:05.224 --> 12:07.726
Four criminals?
Working together?

12:07.810 --> 12:09.728
This is serious.

12:09.812 --> 12:12.648
{\an1}They're trying to make it
look like we're the robbers.

12:12.731 --> 12:14.316
Hmm.

12:17.069 --> 12:18.320
I believe you're innocent,
Fresh Beats.

12:18.404 --> 12:19.822
[Fresh Beats sigh]

12:19.905 --> 12:23.075
But the rest of the city
thinks you're crooks.

12:23.159 --> 12:24.493
You have to catch
these fake Fresh Beats,

12:24.577 --> 12:28.372
or I'll have to arrest you.

12:28.456 --> 12:30.666
Here.
Take this gold star.

12:30.750 --> 12:31.459
It's how I'll know
you're the real

12:31.542 --> 12:34.003
Fresh Beat Band of Spies.

12:34.086 --> 12:35.504
Don't worry,
Commissioner Goldstar,

12:35.588 --> 12:38.007
we'll solve this case
and clear our names.

12:38.090 --> 12:40.342
Yeah!
We'll, uh, uh--

12:40.426 --> 12:41.177
How are we gonna catch them?

12:41.260 --> 12:44.054
Hmm.
Time to disguise it up!

12:45.139 --> 12:46.307
Time now for the

12:46.390 --> 12:48.100
{\an1}Muse and Cruise
Newsy-News News Crew

12:48.184 --> 12:50.060
{\an1}with Jack Muse
and Jackie Cruise!

12:50.144 --> 12:51.187
I'm Jack Muse.

12:51.270 --> 12:52.229
And I'm Jackie Cruise.

12:52.313 --> 12:54.690
{\an3}Our top story,
the Fresh Beat Band

12:54.774 --> 12:55.357
has been found completely

12:55.441 --> 12:56.859
and totally innocent

12:56.942 --> 12:59.361
{\an3}of the bank
and diamond store robberies.

12:59.445 --> 13:00.863
That's right, Jackie.

13:00.946 --> 13:04.241
Instead of being arrested,
they're giving a big free

13:04.325 --> 13:07.703
{\an1}charity toy drive concert
at the amusement park tomorrow.

13:07.786 --> 13:09.038
{\an3}How nice.

13:09.121 --> 13:11.040
{\an1}So make sure you come down
for the totally innocent

13:11.123 --> 13:15.294
{\an1}Fresh Beat Band's
big free charity toy concert

13:15.377 --> 13:17.880
{\an1}at the amusement park
tomorrow.

13:17.963 --> 13:19.423
Von terrible!

13:19.507 --> 13:22.301
How can that newslady say
the Fresh Beats are innocent?

13:22.384 --> 13:23.469
The police are
supposed to think

13:23.552 --> 13:26.388
they robbed the bank
and the diamond store!

13:26.472 --> 13:27.681
{\an3}Arrrgh!

13:27.765 --> 13:29.183
This makes me...

13:29.266 --> 13:32.686
♪ The most angry
singing pirate captain ♪

13:32.770 --> 13:33.562
♪ Disguised as a spy ♪

13:33.646 --> 13:36.232
♪ In the world! ♪

13:36.315 --> 13:38.651
[clucks]

13:38.734 --> 13:41.403
Hey, that's my
ultra-gigantic television!

13:41.487 --> 13:45.157
Your von plan
is not von working!

13:45.241 --> 13:46.909
[rapid mumbling]

13:46.992 --> 13:47.910
[chuckles]

13:47.993 --> 13:50.538
My plan is von working.

13:50.621 --> 13:51.372
Where did Rudy go?

13:51.455 --> 13:54.124
And why am I there,

13:54.208 --> 13:55.751
when I am here?

13:55.834 --> 13:57.002
{\an1}Not there.

13:57.086 --> 13:57.962
Wait a minute.

13:58.045 --> 13:59.255
You aren't me.

13:59.338 --> 14:02.049
{\an1}You are you pretending
to be me.

14:02.132 --> 14:03.259
Are you von certain?

14:03.342 --> 14:06.053
{\an1}Uh, no?

14:06.136 --> 14:09.932
{\an1}Yes! Yes, I am von sure
I am von me.

14:10.015 --> 14:11.183
I von think.

14:11.267 --> 14:13.686
{\an1}You are making
my von brain hurt.

14:13.769 --> 14:15.145
[rapid mumbling]

14:15.229 --> 14:17.273
Ha, ha!
Fooled ya!

14:17.356 --> 14:19.775
Face it.
I'm a genius.

14:19.858 --> 14:21.277
What's the big deal?

14:21.360 --> 14:23.779
We put on our Fresh Beats
disguises one more time,

14:23.862 --> 14:25.197
[rapid mumbling]

14:25.281 --> 14:27.533
go to the concert,
and we make them look so bad

14:27.616 --> 14:29.451
they'll go to jail
for a long time.

14:29.535 --> 14:30.619
So who's ready
to rock and roll?

14:30.703 --> 14:34.540
♪ Me, me, me, me! ♪

14:34.623 --> 14:36.500
Rock und roll!

14:36.584 --> 14:37.585
Yee-haw!

14:39.545 --> 14:40.713
This is great.

14:40.796 --> 14:43.132
We'll catch those crooks

14:43.215 --> 14:45.467
and collect lots of toys
for kids.

14:45.551 --> 14:49.555
{\an5}(male announcer)
Ladies and gentlemen,
the Fresh Beat Band!

14:49.638 --> 14:51.890
Oh, I love that band!

14:51.974 --> 14:53.142
Wait.
That band is us.

14:53.225 --> 14:55.686
{\an1}Must be the fake Fresh Beats.
Let's go!

14:56.729 --> 15:00.024
[crowd murmuring indistinctly]

15:00.107 --> 15:01.150
[cheering]

15:01.233 --> 15:02.151
Heh.
Thank you!

15:02.234 --> 15:04.820
Thanks for bringing
all these toys.

15:04.903 --> 15:08.574
We're gonna make sure they get
to very special boys and girls.

15:08.657 --> 15:10.117
Like us!

15:10.200 --> 15:11.160
{\an1}Thank you very much!
Lasso!

15:11.243 --> 15:13.537
Yee-haw!

15:14.580 --> 15:17.082
Hardy-har-har-har!

15:17.166 --> 15:18.083
Fog cannon!

15:18.167 --> 15:19.251
Ar-har-har!

15:19.335 --> 15:21.378
[audience coughing]

15:21.462 --> 15:22.046
Let's go!

15:22.129 --> 15:24.006
[audience coughing]

15:24.089 --> 15:25.382
The Fresh Beat Band

15:25.466 --> 15:27.384
took all the toys with them!

15:27.468 --> 15:30.888
[audience talking all at once]

15:30.971 --> 15:32.973
Oh, we missed
the fake Fresh Beats!

15:33.057 --> 15:34.850
They already took off
with the toys.

15:34.933 --> 15:37.436
(audience member)
It's them!

15:37.519 --> 15:38.812
- Give us the toys back!
- What's going on?

15:38.896 --> 15:41.273
This isn't
how it looks!

15:41.357 --> 15:42.358
We'll get those toys back.

15:42.441 --> 15:44.485
{\an1}And we'll be back
to play a great concert.

15:44.568 --> 15:46.695
We promise.

15:46.779 --> 15:47.071
(audience member)
Why'd you do that?

15:50.282 --> 15:51.200
[rapid mumbling]

15:51.283 --> 15:53.869
This way!

15:53.952 --> 15:54.870
This way!

15:54.953 --> 15:55.037
They're over there!

15:57.706 --> 16:00.084
{\an5}(woman over radio)
Keep an eye out
for the Fresh Beat Band.

16:00.167 --> 16:01.627
If you see 'em, grab 'em!

16:01.710 --> 16:03.337
Loud and clear,
over and out.

16:05.798 --> 16:06.507
[thud]

16:06.590 --> 16:07.883
(all)
[grunts]

16:07.966 --> 16:09.218
[rapid mumbling]

16:09.301 --> 16:10.719
Hold it right there!

16:10.803 --> 16:12.137
{\an1}The Fresh Beat Band,
you're wanted for robbery.

16:12.221 --> 16:16.100
Officer, I can explain
everything, you see--

16:16.183 --> 16:17.101
Good job, officer!

16:17.184 --> 16:19.353
You got 'em!

16:19.436 --> 16:21.021
What is going on here?

16:21.105 --> 16:23.065
Oh, I'm seeing double.

16:23.148 --> 16:24.191
Those guys are fakes.

16:24.274 --> 16:26.026
We're the real Fresh Beats.

16:26.110 --> 16:26.985
You are?

16:27.069 --> 16:28.320
{\an3}Absolutely!

16:28.404 --> 16:30.114
Then you're under arrest,
you can go.

16:30.197 --> 16:31.782
Wait. No.
Wait. What?

16:31.865 --> 16:33.367
{\an3}Look.
Those are the bad guys.

16:33.450 --> 16:34.868
We're the good guys.

16:34.952 --> 16:38.414
Good guys don't rob banks
and diamond stores.

16:38.497 --> 16:39.456
Where'd they go?

16:39.540 --> 16:40.541
Commissioner Goldstar,

16:40.624 --> 16:43.460
I've got
the Fresh Beats right here.

16:43.544 --> 16:45.087
The real Fresh Beat Band!

16:45.170 --> 16:46.588
Let 'em go.

16:46.672 --> 16:47.923
They're after a gang
of serious criminals.

16:48.006 --> 16:50.968
(Fresh Beats)
Thanks, Commissioner!

16:51.051 --> 16:52.428
I need a vacation.

16:52.511 --> 16:53.721
Quick, in here!

16:53.804 --> 16:55.931
[rapid mumbling]

16:56.014 --> 16:58.934
[intense music]

16:59.017 --> 17:03.480
♪ ♪

17:03.564 --> 17:04.106
There they go!

17:06.191 --> 17:09.028
We're gonna need
that lasso again.

17:09.111 --> 17:12.823
I'm as ready as a buckin' bronco
on rodeo day.

17:12.906 --> 17:15.951
They got off the Ferris wheel!

17:16.034 --> 17:17.869
[grunts]
Got it!

17:17.953 --> 17:19.747
Now we pull!

17:19.829 --> 17:21.415
Von pulling!

17:21.498 --> 17:24.126
Anchors away!

17:24.209 --> 17:25.586
[rope snaps]

17:25.669 --> 17:28.672
(all)
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

17:28.756 --> 17:32.134
(all)
[groaning]

17:32.217 --> 17:35.053
Oh, come on,

17:35.137 --> 17:36.597
let's get 'em!

17:36.680 --> 17:38.223
(all)
Oof!

17:38.307 --> 17:41.727
(all)
[groaning]

17:41.810 --> 17:44.146
[groans]

17:44.229 --> 17:45.814
[chatters]

17:45.898 --> 17:48.734
Come on!
We'll lose 'em in the fun house!

17:48.817 --> 17:52.821
[suspenseful music]

17:52.905 --> 17:59.870
♪ ♪

17:59.953 --> 18:01.497
Hmm?

18:01.580 --> 18:04.583
Oh, pretending to be a mirror,

18:04.666 --> 18:06.376
eh, Captain Arrrgh?

18:06.460 --> 18:07.169
[chatters]

18:07.252 --> 18:09.379
Right.
And Poulet?

18:09.463 --> 18:11.465
Gotcha!

18:11.548 --> 18:12.841
Ho-ho, pretty clever.

18:12.925 --> 18:18.388
But not clever enough!

18:18.472 --> 18:20.516
[laughs evilly]

18:20.599 --> 18:24.686
I did not see that coming.

18:24.770 --> 18:25.938
(Twist)
♪ Move it, move it ♪

18:26.021 --> 18:27.105
♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh ♪

18:27.189 --> 18:28.190
♪ Hey! ♪

18:28.273 --> 18:29.233
♪ Here we go ♪

18:29.316 --> 18:32.820
♪ Stand up
It's time to go ♪

18:32.903 --> 18:34.112
♪ On your mark
Get set ♪

18:34.196 --> 18:36.073
♪ Let's move ♪

18:36.156 --> 18:37.199
[groans]

18:37.282 --> 18:38.492
If we're going to catch
those crooks,

18:38.575 --> 18:39.326
we're gonna need more speed!

18:39.409 --> 18:41.411
Turbo power?
Coming up!

18:41.495 --> 18:44.206
Thanks to my
turbo-nana!

18:44.289 --> 18:46.750
[electronic buzzing]

18:46.834 --> 18:48.710
(all)
Whoo!

18:48.794 --> 18:51.338
They are von gaining on us!

18:51.421 --> 18:52.297
Captain Arrrgh,

18:52.381 --> 18:54.424
time to make an egg-scape!

18:54.508 --> 18:55.384
Aye, aye!

18:55.467 --> 18:57.845
Lay it on 'em, Poulet.

18:57.928 --> 18:59.388
[clucks]

18:59.471 --> 19:01.181
[splat]

19:01.265 --> 19:02.307
♪ It's time to move it ♪

19:02.391 --> 19:04.059
♪ It's time to groove it ♪

19:04.143 --> 19:05.227
♪ Are you ready? ♪

19:05.310 --> 19:05.811
♪ 'Cause here we go ♪

19:05.894 --> 19:08.063
♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh ♪

19:08.146 --> 19:09.064
That's enough!

19:09.147 --> 19:12.109
Von losing control!

19:12.192 --> 19:14.695
(all)
Whoa!

19:14.778 --> 19:15.529
They're going off the track!

19:15.612 --> 19:18.031
We've got to follow them!

19:18.115 --> 19:19.283
[Bo chatters nervously]

19:19.366 --> 19:20.909
[all yelling]

19:20.993 --> 19:21.618
Oh, no!

19:21.702 --> 19:22.995
The gold star!

19:23.078 --> 19:25.956
Now how will we prove
that we're the real Fresh Beats?

19:26.039 --> 19:27.207
Time for a change!

19:27.291 --> 19:27.374
[rapid mumbling]

19:29.459 --> 19:30.878
[thuds]

19:30.961 --> 19:33.463
♪ ♪

19:33.547 --> 19:35.173
{\an1}Commissioner Goldstar,
those are the crooks

19:35.257 --> 19:37.968
{\an1}who robbed the bank
and the diamond store.

19:38.051 --> 19:39.177
Arrest them!

19:39.261 --> 19:40.178
{\an3}No!
Commissioner,

19:40.262 --> 19:41.221
they're the crooks.

19:41.305 --> 19:42.681
They're trying to fool you.

19:42.764 --> 19:44.766
All right, well,
who's got the gold star?

19:44.850 --> 19:46.476
{\an1}[sighs]
We lost it.

19:46.560 --> 19:47.978
[groans]

19:48.061 --> 19:51.356
Well, how am I supposed to know

19:51.440 --> 19:52.941
which of you is which?

19:53.025 --> 19:54.151
We'll prove we're
the real Fresh Beats.

19:54.234 --> 19:57.112
{\an1}We challenge these
fake Fresh Beats

19:57.195 --> 19:58.947
to a battle of the bands!

19:59.031 --> 19:59.907
{\an3}Ha, no!

19:59.990 --> 20:01.491
We challenge you

20:01.575 --> 20:02.284
to a battle of the bands!

20:02.367 --> 20:05.287
No, dude.
Too late.

20:05.370 --> 20:06.663
We already cha--

20:07.873 --> 20:10.959
[laughs nervously]
Arrrgh you ready to rock?

20:11.043 --> 20:13.337
(off-tune)
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:13.420 --> 20:14.338
♪ No matter what I do ♪

20:14.421 --> 20:17.299
(on-tune)
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:17.382 --> 20:18.300
♪ I'm always here for you ♪

20:18.383 --> 20:21.428
(off-tune)
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:21.511 --> 20:23.388
♪ No matter what I do ♪

20:23.472 --> 20:24.264
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:24.348 --> 20:25.515
Give me that, ugh--
[grunts]

20:25.599 --> 20:27.809
{\an1}Um...

20:27.893 --> 20:29.311
♪ You need an ear?
You can call me ♪

20:29.394 --> 20:31.063
♪ Or you need somebody near?
Never fear, man, it's all me! ♪

20:31.146 --> 20:32.314
♪ I'll be there, buddy, really ♪

20:32.397 --> 20:34.942
♪ You need a joke?
Knock, knock! ♪

20:35.025 --> 20:36.485
- ♪ Who's there? ♪
- ♪ Me, silly! ♪

20:36.568 --> 20:38.278
- ♪ You need some time ♪
- ♪ Tick, tick, we can talk ♪

20:38.362 --> 20:39.279
♪ Round the clock ♪

20:39.363 --> 20:40.322
Clocks and rocks and socks--

20:40.405 --> 20:41.531
Tick around the clock--

20:41.615 --> 20:43.033
♪ 'Cause you've been with me ♪

20:43.116 --> 20:44.368
♪ From the start
In the middle of my heart ♪

20:44.451 --> 20:46.495
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:46.578 --> 20:47.913
(off-tune)
♪ No matter what I do ♪

20:47.996 --> 20:48.956
{\an3}(on-tune)
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:49.039 --> 20:51.833
♪ I'll be here for you ♪

20:51.917 --> 20:53.794
♪ Hey now, hey now now ♪

20:53.877 --> 20:56.380
♪ No matter what I do ♪

20:56.463 --> 20:58.340
(all)
Whoa!

20:58.423 --> 21:01.134
♪ I'll be here for you ♪

21:01.218 --> 21:06.181
♪ La-la-la-la! ♪

21:06.264 --> 21:07.182
{\an1}Arrrgh!

21:07.265 --> 21:08.308
[cheering]

21:08.392 --> 21:09.142
Well, audience,

21:09.226 --> 21:11.687
are the real Fresh Beats here?

21:11.770 --> 21:13.563
Aye!

21:13.647 --> 21:15.190
[booing]

21:15.273 --> 21:17.192
Or here?

21:17.275 --> 21:18.527
[applause, cheering]

21:18.610 --> 21:18.944
(all)
Yeah!

21:19.027 --> 21:21.822
{\an3}I agree.

21:23.657 --> 21:24.992
Von Winnerchamp!

21:25.075 --> 21:26.159
Yi-Haw!

21:26.243 --> 21:28.161
And Captain Arrrgh.

21:28.245 --> 21:29.413
[chatters, clucks]

21:29.496 --> 21:30.789
[rapid mumbling]

21:30.872 --> 21:32.416
{\an3}(Commissioner)
Rubberface Rudy,

21:32.499 --> 21:33.875
face it.

21:33.959 --> 21:35.210
Your days of crime
are over.

21:35.293 --> 21:39.339
{\an1}Now, let's hand out
those toys.

21:39.423 --> 21:40.590
Face it.

21:40.674 --> 21:41.758
This is a mess.

21:41.842 --> 21:45.220
{\an3}[crying]

21:45.303 --> 21:46.304
[all screams]

21:46.388 --> 21:46.805
Von dunking...

21:46.888 --> 21:47.764
Whoo-hoo!

21:47.848 --> 21:50.392
[all scream]

21:50.475 --> 21:54.730
{\an1}♪ The wettest
singing pirate captain ♪

21:54.813 --> 21:58.233
♪ In the world! ♪

21:58.317 --> 21:59.401
{\an1}[spits]

21:59.484 --> 22:00.402
[applause, cheering]

22:00.485 --> 22:02.279
What a great mission!

22:02.362 --> 22:02.696
What a great concert!

22:02.779 --> 22:04.698
[laughs]

22:04.781 --> 22:05.532
What a great day!

22:09.036 --> 22:09.953
(Fresh Beat Band)
♪ We had a great day ♪

22:10.037 --> 22:13.123
♪ It was a super way ♪

22:13.206 --> 22:17.669
♪ To spend some time together ♪

22:17.753 --> 22:20.756
♪ La, la-la-la-la-la ♪

22:20.839 --> 22:22.382
♪ Hey ♪

22:22.466 --> 22:23.550
♪ Great day ♪

22:23.633 --> 22:24.801
♪ A great, great day ♪

22:24.885 --> 22:25.761
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

22:25.844 --> 22:27.012
♪ Great day ♪

